                            <p>The simple search enables you to identify all instances of a particular term or code from
                                within our network of mapped standards. So, you can search for ‘health’ and be shown
                                every occurrence of that term in the standards we have mapped (or within grouped
                                ‘projects’). For example, when searching for ‘health’ within our ‘sectors’ project, the
                                results will include:
                            </p>

                            <img src="resource/images/image1.png" alt="adasda" class="image-sizing">

                            <p>From there you can click an individual ‘concept’ or occurrence from within the search
                                results:
                            </p>

                            <img src="resource/images/image3.png" alt="adasda" class="image-sizing">

                            <p>And explore how it relates to fields in other standards:</p>

                            <img src="resource/images/image2.png" alt="adasda" class="image-sizing">

                            <p>Simple search allows you either to look for a specific project or browse for a specific
                                term (or code) across projects.
                            </p>

